  Army Staff Sgt Julian McDonald of Columbus, Ohio has welcomed a Belgian Malinois named Layka into his home . 
  Layka was on her eighth overseas tour with him in 2012 when she was shot four times at point blank range by an enemy fighter . 
  She lost her front leg in the attack and had to have it amputated . 
  McDonald decided to adopt Layka after fighting to adopt her . 
 